# Multi-tier-App-Jenkins-CICD:

› Usable elements -> AWS + EKS(K8S) + Docker + DockerHub + Maven + Git + Jenkins
› Create a new VPC
› Create private and public subnets
› Create InternetGateWay and NatGateWay 
› Create RDS MySQL inside the same VPC(private)
› Create Jenkins Ec2 server in public subnet
› Install Jenkins, Docker, kubectl, aws CLI on Ec2
› Connect Jenkins —> EKS —> RDS 

*Sign in to AWS Web Console

# VPC Creation Steps :

› VPC name : multi-tier-cicd-vpc  
› CIDR Range : 10.0.0.0/16
› 4 subnets —> 2 public subnets and 2 private subnets
› public-subnet-a(10.0.1.0/24) and public-subnet-b(10.0.2.0/24)
› private-subnet-a(10.0.3.0/24) and private-subnet-b(10.0.4.0/24)
› Edit VPC settings : Enable DNS hostname
› IGW (Internet Gateway) : multi-tier-cicd-IGW
› Attach IGW to multi-tier-cicd-vpc (for Accessibility)
› Go to Route table 
› Rename the pc associated route table to public-route-table
› Select Routes —> Edit Routes —> All Traffic(0.0.0.0) to IGW (multi-tier-cicd-IGW) 
› Now go to the subnet associations 
› Edit subnet associations and attach both public subnets —> Save Association
› NAT Gateway : multi-tier-cicd-NGW
› Availability Mode : Zonal
› Subnet : public-subnet-a
› Allocate public ip > Create Nat Gateway
› Create a Route Table : private-route-table
› Edit Routes : 0.0.0.0 > Nat Gateway
› Edit Subnet Assoiations : Add both private subnets (a and b)
› So,by now VPC has been fully configured



